# Local Workspace — Environment Variables
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# NEVER commit .env — it is gitignored.
#
# This file is the shared catalog of credentials used by local integrations.
# When you add a new integration, add its variable names here (no values)
# so other operators know what credentials are available.
#
# Lifecycle:
#   1. Add your credential here and to your local .env
#   2. Use it in .mcp.json (env field) or your tool script (os.environ)
#   3. When the tool is promoted to the remote gateway, the admin provisions
#      the same variable on the server
#   4. After promotion, remove the local MCP entry from .mcp.json — the
#      gateway handles the integration from that point forward

# =============================================================================
# Remote Gateway
# =============================================================================
# The gateway URL is set in .mcp.json — no env var needed here.

# =============================================================================
# Stripe
# =============================================================================
# STRIPE_API_KEY=sk_test_...

# =============================================================================
# HubSpot
# =============================================================================
# HUBSPOT_ACCESS_TOKEN=pat-na1-...

# =============================================================================
# Snowflake
# =============================================================================
# SNOWFLAKE_ACCOUNT=yourorg.us-east-1
# SNOWFLAKE_USER=
# SNOWFLAKE_PASSWORD=
# SNOWFLAKE_DATABASE=
# SNOWFLAKE_WAREHOUSE=

# =============================================================================
# Postgres
# =============================================================================
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/dbname

# =============================================================================
# Exa
# =============================================================================
# EXA_API_KEY=your-exa-api-key

# =============================================================================
# Add new integrations below this line
# =============================================================================
